page.title: 05FLORA AND FAUNA
page.content: Flowers and trees, animals and birds are those found in North England. Common {PLANTS}include:- Buttercup,Poppy,Spurge,Lily,Arum,Ivy, Fumitory,Dock,Orchid,Cabbage,Nettle, Violet,Heath,Daisy,Milkwort,Primrose, Pink,Borage,Mallow,Figwort,Geranium, Broomrape,Woodsorrel,Thyme,Balsam, Peaflower,Plantain,Rose,Teasel,Stonecr op,Saxifrage,Bellflower, Willowherb, Bedstraw,Honeysuckle,Cow Parsley and Umbellifers, grasses,reeds. {TREES}include Birch,Elm,Hazel, Beech, Willow, Olive, Horsechestnut, Cypress, Pine,Lime and Maple. {BIRDS}include game birds,common Northern birds,oyster catchers. {ANIMALS}-adders,grass snakes,rodents {FISH}-plentiful brown and sea trout,salmon.
